						               													<description>Platoon level World War 2 miniature wargames rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Troops, Weapons &amp;amp; Tactics (TW&amp;amp;T) is not just a rule set. With 108 pages, 40 of which are in full colour, the gamer gets the rules, stats for Britain, Germany, the USSR and the USA for the 1944 and '45 period, a scenario and force generation system along with an introduction to the forces as they were historically organised and the tactics that they used.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;TW&amp;amp;T, like its stablemate I Ain't Been Shot Mum (IABSM), uses a card driven system that produces a variable turn sequence. Unlike IABSM each squad leader is represented along with the platoon officer and Sergeant. These leaders use a system of Tactical Initiatives to motivate and activate their men on the battlefield.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expanded by:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Rock the Casbah: Modern Urban Warfare in the Lebanese Civil War&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
